@aviemzur the while behaviour of `PipelineResult` is up for refactor as it behaves weird now (in the SDK, not specifically the Spark runner).
So it is a good question if you should stop after timeout passed..  what if the user wants to wait 10 seconds or until done (whichever comes first) and then do his thing ? makes sense... so stopping is not the solution.
See [BEAM-849](https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/BEAM-849)
